<title type="html"><![CDATA[5/9(Sat.)Board game&quot;Who Is Spy&quot;/Garnishing cocktails with edible insects. Host:Nora]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=389&amp;p=406#p406"><![CDATA[
5/9(Sat.)Board game&quot;Who Is Spy&quot;/Garnishing cocktails with edible insects. Host:Nora<br />Session 1.<br />Hello everyone, we had played the classic board game &quot;Werewolves of Miller's Hollow &quot; and this Saturday, we are going to have another popular board game &quot;Who Is Spy&quot;.(game description below)<br /><br />Getting bored of staying home all the time? Come here to join us with your masks on, let's have something new this Saturday. <br /><br />Session 2.<br />Garnishing cocktails with edible insects <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/aR-NubbhYco">https://youtu.be/aR-NubbhYco</a><!-- m --><br /><br />This video shows that a younger bartender from Singapore uses unusual ingredients to get interesting flavors. <br /><br />Questions:<br />1. Have you eaten something unusual? How do you feel? Share your experience <br />2. If you have chance to taste these special food will you give yourself a try? And why? <br />3. Do you hear about any other strange food? <br /><br />Description of Who Is Spy:<br />In this game, there are two roles, mortals and spies.<br />Each of you will have a piece of paper, and you are not allowed to show it to anyone, keep it secret. <br /><br />There is a picture and vocabulary on the paper, try to describe in one sentence without talking about the name.<br /><br />You will have no idea if you are the spy or not. So pay attention to others' comment.<br /><br />After a round, participators should vote who is most likely be the spy.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25764">Michelle Hsu</a> — Mon May 04, 2020 9:34 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
